INSERT INTO `text` VALUES (133,'Proteins are very important macro-molecules that are behind most of the processes that occur in living organisms. Amino Acids (AAs) covalently bonded in a chain form the primary structure of proteins. Nevertheless, in order to perform their function, proteins adopt a three dimensional structure that is determined by non-covalent interactions occurring between the atoms that compose the AAs. This three dimensional structure is not static, the different residues can move, and thus, stabilize or break non-covalent interactions. Molecular Dynamics (MD) is a computational technique widely used to simulate these movements at atomic resolution. However, it is very difficult to gather relevant structural and functional information from MD simulations and several tools are often required to perform these highly complex analyses. RIP-MD allows to apply Residue Interaction Networks (RINs) to the analysis of MD simulations of protein. The non-covalent interactions defined by RIP-MD include Hydrogen bonds, Salt bridges, van der Waals contacts, cation-π, π-π, Arginine-Arginine and Coulomb interactions. In addition, RIP-MD also computes interactions based on distances between Cαs and disulfide bridges. The results of the analysis are shown in an user friendly way. The user can take advantage of the VMD visualization capacities, whereby going through some effortless steps, selected interactions described for a single, several or all residues can be shown. Network and table files are also generated, allowing their study in platforms such as Cytoscape. RIP-MD method was written in python in a highly parallelized fashion. This characteristic, combined with the possibility of calling the method outside VMD, permits to benefit from the use of HPC infrastructures and grants the analysis of very large systems impossible to handle otherwise.\n\n== Download RIP-MD ==\n\nRIP-MD is available in two different flavors, as a VMD plugin or as a standalone software.\n\nIn the next section you can download the latest version of RIP-MD. Also you can follow the project at GitHub\n\nTo install it, you need to uncompress the downloaded file (or clone RIP-MD from GitHub) and follow installation instructions in the [http://146.83.236.3/ripmd/files/manual.pdf RIP-MD manual].\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Format!!Standalone!!VMD plugin\n|-\n|RAR||[http://146.83.236.3/ripmd/files/RIP-MD-standalone-1.0.2.rar Download]||[http://146.83.236.3/ripmd/files/RIP-MD-plugin-1.0.2.rar Download]\n|-\n|ZIP||[http://146.83.236.3/ripmd/files/RIP-MD-standalone-1.0.2.zip Download]||[http://146.83.236.3/ripmd/files/RIP-MD-plugin-1.0.2.zip Download]\n|-\n|TAR.GZ||[http://146.83.236.3/ripmd/files/RIP-MD-standalone-1.0.2.tar.gz Download]||[http://146.83.236.3/ripmd/files/RIP-MD-plugin-1.0.2.tar.gz Download]\n|-\n|GitHub||you can go to the project clicking [https://github.com/DLab/RIP-MD-standalone- Here]||you can go to the project clicking [https://github.com/DLab/RIP-MD-plugin- Here]\n|}\n\n== Download User Manual ==\n\nTo download the User Manual of RIM-MD, click [http://146.83.236.3/ripmd/files/manual.pdf Here]\n\n== Supplementary Data ==\n\n=== MD2 supplementary data ===\n\n==== Molecular Dynamics Files ====\n\nTo download MD2 dcd file, please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TejRXOFNvMHBjUEU Here].\n\nTo download MD2 psf file, please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TRzA2SFQ0SVNVQTA Here].\n\n==== RIP-MD results for MD2 experiments ====\n\nTo download RIP-MD results for the first window (from 0 to 1250 ps of the simulation), please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TS2h3cWs3M0VMSEE Here].\n\nTo download RIP-MD results for the second window (from 1250 to 12500 ps of the simulation), please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TMlJNMlBEb1lZQ00 Here].\n\nTo download RIP-MD results for the third window (from 12500 ps until the end of the simulation), please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TUFozanNSbWlmY0U Here].\n\n==== MD2 for Pearson graphs ====\n\nHere you can download cytoscape sessions for absolute pearson values graphs respect to HB and VdW interactions\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Absolute Pearson Value\n!Cytoscape sessions for the three windows\n|-\n|≥ 0.5 	\n|[https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TWFRaNnNIOWQ4Ukk Download sessions clicking here].\n|-\n|≥ 0.6 	\n|[https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TM09VR3c2Y1FaOFk Download sessions clicking here].\n|-\n|≥ 0.7 	\n|[https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TellzYXdUS3BJM2M Download sessions clicking here].\n|-\n|≥ 0.8\n|[https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TTWMtS1VtNnpIWnM Download sessions clicking here].\n|-\n|≥ 0.9\n|[https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_N897Yoeg-TalU5MTUwSF9rSTQ/view Download sessions clicking here].\n|}\n\n=== GJC supplementary data ===\n\n==== Molecular Dynamics Files ====\n\nTo download GJC dcd file, please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TVTFoX3YwRlJ0aG8 Here].\n\nTo download GJC psf file, please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TQ1IyczBEd2VXQVk Here].\n\nTo download GJC pdb file, please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TR3pPRENhM3lwLUk Here].\n\n==== RIP-MD results for GJC experiments ====\n\nTo download RIP-MD results for the GJC model, please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TdWRkVjBLT3hjSlk Here].\n\nTo download RIP-MD results for the GJC MD, please click [https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_N897Yoeg-TV3NCeWNmaVRMMlU Here].\n\n== Terms of Use and Legal Notices ==\n\n=== RIP-MD Terms of Use and Legal Notices ===\n\nAs \'\'\'RIP-MD\'\'\' is provided without charge, by using it you agree that any warranty is excluded, regarding to functionality or fitness for purpose or otherwise.\n\nAlso, we collect some data which will be used exclusively by us to keep track of the usage of our different services, and to protect us against abuse of our services